### ‚úÖ **ESLint Boundary Enforcement**

There is **no ‚Äúofficial built-in rule‚Äù** for cross-project import boundaries ‚Äî you must choose a specific plugin/apprach. A strong option is:

- üü¢ **eslint-plugin-boundaries (GitHub)**
  [https://github.com/bryanrsmith/eslint-plugin-boundaries](https://github.com/bryanrsmith/eslint-plugin-boundaries)

‚Üí This is community-maintained but widely used for boundary enforcement.

Alternatively, consider:

- **eslint-plugin-import**
  [https://github.com/import-js/eslint-plugin-import](https://github.com/import-js/eslint-plugin-import)

Both are valid; your internal doc should compare them.

